public interface TreeRenderer<T extends TreeRenderable>

Note - rather than having this in a separate class to the (CriteriaGroup) object, these methods are kept in the class for easier overriding - even though the classes can get sorta messy. Otherwise access can be a problem. Remember, criteriagroups are really more UI objects, it's the criterion that count more in search (if using projections). umm...now I'm not convinced neither. ok, all detached...
